snippet.textDisplay: I never order seafood when i eat out. The only time i do is at an expensive place known for seafood. I worked with seafood long enough to know it is very difficult to find someone in charge of the fish you are consuming that is actually worried about selling you bad fish. This is just at fish markets, now imagine a restaurant that may not be able to get fish straight off boats or from a vendor that only does fish. And, in my experience, the more expensive and high end the fish, the more of a chance you will get it when it is already bad. They dont want to lose money, so they keep it out as long as possible and freshen it up whatever way they can.

snippet.textDisplay:
The Independent People’s Tribunal, also known as the China Tribunal, is the first independent tribunal to examine evidence of the Chinese regime's targeting of innocent prisoners of conscience to forcibly harvest their organs for transplantation.

Public hearings for the China Tribunal started on December 8, 2018, and ran for three days, during which more than 30 witnesses, including refugees, investigators and doctors presented disturbing evidence.

Following the hearing, scholars and experts condemned the crimes of forced organ harvesting in China, hoping to alert people around the world to the crimes committed by the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) and calling for legal measures against the persecution.

The final judgment of the tribunal is due in spring 2019.


Sir Geoffrey Nice QC, chair of the Independent People's Tribunal, also known as the China Tribunal, announces an interim judgment.

Legal Counsel to Tribunal: Let the Public Know What Has Happened

snippet.textDisplay: I don’t even keep leftovers for more than 3 days in my fridge ! Even at home I will immediately throw out food and drink if even the slightest off smell or look etc! I’m extremely extremely picky about food and drinks at my house I’ll throw out ice even if it makes my drink taste off! I have a very sensitive palate too! I can pick up salt very easy found out a lot of restaurants over season food with salt !

snippet.textDisplay:
Thank you chef Ramsey! I learned from watching your shows! If it not hot don’t eat it if it smells bad don’t eat it if it’s not cold don’t eat it ! have saved myself from a lot of health issues! I now make it a point I’ll make Resturant make me a new dish completely hot or cold or whatever I call restaurants out now ! Last night I ripped my local restaurant a new one for serving me meat when I’m vegan! Told them to make me a dish with no meat no dairy and they did and they served my husband his dish was ice cold I raised hell with owner they corrected the issues and I got the meal free of charge even fresh made ! So my advice is to always hold every restaurant you go to in high standards if it’s not hot or cold or fresh food RAISE hell!!! YOUR life could be at stake and save yourself from being horribly sick!
I’m a huge stickler on food now when I go out to eat I even tell staff I’m not paying or giving a tip or anything else if I’m paying for a meal it better be too service and top notch food I Don’t take food service and drink lightly! Yes some Restaurants hate me but I don’t care I’m paying for a meal as a customer and I deserve the best otherwise they don’t get my money! I’ve walked out of 5 restaurants near me and reported a lot to health department because they can’t keep food temperature or fresh ingredients! I literally no joke carry a list with me of about 3 restaurants I will eat at near me because I know they do a amazing food service job! Call me a bitch or whatever but sorry I don’t think it’s a bad thing to make sure you don’t get sick from good and drink! and I encourage everyone to for lack or better words be a jerk if you have to to make sure your food and drink are prepared properly! touch it smell it taste it I say! if it’s not to your standards then call the chefs and owners out! I’m so very grateful for chef Ramsey he is amazing he’s showing that we should take our food and drink VERY seriously! He has my utmost respect! thank you chef Ramsey for what you do for people!
